    {
      "title": "Form VII Verbs (اِنْفَعَلَ)",
      "titleArabic": "الفعل في الباب السابع",
      "content": [
        "Form VII verbs follow the pattern اِنْفَعَلَ - يَنْفَعِلُ. This form typically indicates a passive or reflexive meaning - something happening to itself or being affected by an action.",
        "Form VII is often the passive counterpart of Form I verbs."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Past pattern: اِنْفَعَلَ (e.g., اِنْفَتَحَ)",
        "Present pattern: يَنْفَعِلُ (e.g., يَنْفَتِحُ)",
        "Meaning: Passive/reflexive - 'to be done' or 'to become'",
        "فَتَحَ (he opened) → اِنْفَتَحَ (it opened / was opened)",
        "كَسَرَ (he broke) → اِنْكَسَرَ (it broke / was broken)"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "اِنْفَتَحَ الْبَابُ", "english": "The door opened (by itself)" },
        { "arabic": "اِنْكَسَرَ الزُّجَاجُ", "english": "The glass broke" },
        { "arabic": "اِنْقَطَعَ الْحَبْلُ", "english": "The rope was cut / snapped" },
        { "arabic": "اِنْتَهَى الاِجْتِمَاعُ", "english": "The meeting ended" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Characteristics of Form VII",
      "titleArabic": "خصائص الباب السابع",
      "content": [
        "Form VII has specific characteristics that distinguish it from other forms."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Always starts with اِنْـ (in past) or يَنْـ (in present)",
        "Cannot take a direct object (intransitive)",
        "Subject is the one affected by the action",
        "Common verbs: اِنْكَسَرَ، اِنْفَتَحَ، اِنْقَطَعَ، اِنْهَزَمَ"
      ]
    }
  ],
